Description: Defines coding standards and conventions for the Whisper Transcription App.

# Code Conventions

## Python Style

- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines for Python code
- Use 4 spaces for indentation (no tabs)
- Maximum line length of 100 characters
- Use snake_case for functions, methods, and variables
- Use CamelCase for classes
- Use UPPERCASE for constants

## PySide6/Qt Specific

- Use newer style signal/slot connections
- Never directly modify UI elements from worker threads
- Use signals and slots for thread communication
- Prefer programmatic UI construction over .ui files

## Performance and Threading

- Move long-running operations to background threads
- Provide progress feedback for operations over 500ms
- Properly release resources when no longer needed
- Be mindful of memory usage, especially for audio processing
- Cache expensive computations where appropriate
